   - The `<html>` element is the root of the HTML document.
   - The `<head>` element contains meta-information about the document, including the character set, viewport settings, and the title of the page.
   - The `<link>` element is used to link to an external stylesheet.
   - The `<body>` element contains the main content of the page.
   - The `.container` class is used to center the content both horizontally and vertically.
   - The `.header`, `.projects`, and `.footer` classes are used to style the different sections of the page.

2. **Tailwind CSS**:
   - The `@import` statement at the beginning of the `<head>` element imports Tailwind CSS.
   - The `<style>` block within the `<head>` element is used to add custom styles.

3. **Custom CSS**:
   - The custom CSS styles are used to adjust the font size, margin, and padding of the different elements.

